gov.usgs.edge.config

Class SubspaceArea

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.edge.config.SubspaceArea

  • public final class SubspaceArea
extends java.lang.Object
    SubspaceArea.java If the name of the class does not match the name of the field in the class you may need to modify the rs.getSTring in the constructor. This SubspaceArea template for creating a database database object. It is not really needed by the SubspaceAreaPanel which uses the DBObject system for changing a record in the database file. However, you have to have this shell to create objects containing a database record for passing around and manipulating. There are two constructors normally given:
    1) passed a result set positioned to the database record to decode
    2) Passed all of the data arguments needed to build the same set of data.
    The SubspaceArea should be replaced with capitalized version (class name) for the file. subspaceArea should be replaced with the lower case version (for variables). Both the constructors use the "makeSubspaceArea(list of data args) to set the local variables to the value. The result set just uses the rs.get???("fieldname") to get the data from the database where the other passes the arguments from the caller.
    Notes on Enums :
    * data class should have code like :
    import java.util.ArrayList; /// Import for Enum manipulation
    .
    static ArrayList fieldEnum; // This list will have Strings corresponding to enum
    .
    .
    // To convert an enum we need to create the fieldEnum ArrayList. Do only once(static)
    if(fieldEnum == null) fieldEnum = FUtil.getEnum(JDBConnection.getConnection("DATABASE"),"table","fieldName");

    // Get the int corresponding to an Enum String for storage in the data base and
    // the index into the JComboBox representing this Enum
    localVariable = FUtil.enumStringToInt(fieldEnum, enumString);

      • createPreprocessorConfigSB

        public static void createPreprocessorConfigSB(java.sql.Statement stmt,
                                              SubspaceArea area,
                                              SubspaceChannel sschan,
                                              boolean svd,
                                              java.lang.String configPath,
                                              java.lang.String cwbIP,
                                              int cwbPort,
                                              Subspace config,
                                              java.lang.StringBuilder sb,
                                              java.lang.StringBuilder state)
        Given the area, subspacechannel, create an config file suitable for the SubspaceProcessor. If called with a configuration object, it will also populate the SSD CWB if the timeseries is not already there.
        Parameters:
        stmt - An MySQL statement to the Edge database.
        area - An SubspaceArea object for the area that contains this channel
        sschan - The SubspaceChannel for which the config is to be create
        svd - Use svd or independent method
        configPath - Path to put this configuration under
        config - This is the Subspace config record from the subspace table, if present, populate the SSD CWB
        cwbIP - User provided CWBIP for research requests (i.e. not in the subspace configuration table)
        cwbPort - User provide CWB port for research requests
        sb - The user supplied StringBuilder which will contain the configuration string when done, user should clear before calling
        state - The StringBuilder to get the state file contents, NSCL, start and stop times.
